      <h1 class='title'>Bank of England Act 1998 (c. 11)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 18 October 2004 vol 665 c205GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_205gc' title='Col. 205GC &mdash; HL Deb 18 October 2004 vol 665 c205GC' name='column_205gc' href='#column_205gc' rel='bookmark'>205GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05051'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_650' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        In Schedule 7 to the <a href="/acts/bank-of-england-act-1998">Bank of England Act 1998</a> (restriction on disclosure of information), in the table in paragraph 3(1), for the entry relating to the Occupational Pensions Regulatory Authority substitute&#x2014;
      </p>
      
      <div class='table' id='S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_651'>
        <table>
        <tr>
        <td>"The Pensions Regulator</td>
        <td>Functions conferred by or by virtue of&#x2014;</p><p> (a) the <a href="/acts/pension-schemes-act-1993">Pension Schemes Act 1993</a>,</p><p> (b) the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-1995">Pensions Act 1995</a>,</p><p> (c) the <a href="/acts/welfare-reform-and-pensions-act-1999">Welfare Reform and Pensions Act 1999</a>,</p><p> (d) the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-2004">Pensions Act 2004</a>, or</p><p> (e) any enactment in force in Northern Ireland corresponding to an enactment mentioned in paragraphs (a) to (d) above.""</td>
        </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05053'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_652' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 5, at end insert&#x2014;
        <q>In section 8(2)(a) (providing for stakeholder pension schemes to be treated as personal pension schemes), after "is" insert "prescribed or is".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05054'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_653' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 18, at end insert&#x2014;
        <q>( ) in sub-paragraph (i) for the words from "except" to the end substitute "except sections 7(5A)(b), 8(1)(a) and (c) and (2), 11(3A) and (3B) and 15(1);</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05055'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_654' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 20, leave out from "(iii)" to end of line 21 and insert "omit the words from "except" to the end,"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05056'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_655' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, leave out lines 26 and 27 and insert&#x2014;
        <q>(c) the following provisions of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-2004">Pensions Act 2004</a>&#x2014;</q>
        <ol>
        <li>(i) section 61 (accessibility of register of prohibited trustees);</li>
        <li>(ii) Chapters 4 and 5 of Part 2 (fraud compensation and information gathering);</li>
        <li>(iii) sections 236 to 238 (requirements for knowledge and understanding); and</li>
        <li>(iv) section 303 (interpretation).""</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05057'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_656' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 27, at end insert&#x2014;
        <q>( ) In sub-paragraph (5), after "1995 Act" insert", and section 303(1) of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-2004">Pensions Act 2004</a>,".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05058'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_657' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 32, leave out "In Schedule 5, in" and insert&#x2014;
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05059'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_658' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        "(1) Schedule 5 (pension credits: mode of discharge) is amended as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05060'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_659' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05061'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_660' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 34, at end insert&#x2014;
        <q>( ) After paragraph 13 insert&#x2014;</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05062'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_661' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        "13A The provisions of this Schedule are subject to&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) section 73A(3) and (6) of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-1995">Pensions Act 1995</a> (prohibition on new members during winding up of scheme: exception for discharge of pension credit derived from the scheme), and</li>
        <li>(b) section 125(2) and (7A) of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-2004">Pensions Act 2004</a> (prohibition on new members during an assessment period in relation to a scheme: exception for discharge of pension credit derived from the scheme).""</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0665P0-05063'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0665P0_20041018_GCR_662' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 312, line 34, at end insert&#x2014;
      </p>
